</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-2-levels">2-levels dropdown</h2>
	<p>
		It's possible to create 2-levels menu using dropdowns. To add second level menu add <code
		class="format-code">.wds-dropdown-level-2</code> class to <code class="format-code">.wds-list li</code>
		element	and add <code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown-level-2__content</code> element inside
		the list element.
	</p>
	<p>
		2nd level menu is aligned to the top of 1st level dropdown by default, but it doesn't
		work for shorter list so we need to add class <code class="format-code">.wds-is-sticked-to-parent</code>
		to elements that contains shorter level 2 menu. Look at the
		"Broken 2-level" item to see what happens when you don't add that class.
	</p>
	<p>
		2-levels dropdowns do not support shadows and scrollable lists.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle class='push-dropdown-down'}}
				<span>2-levels dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
